The paper introduces a new application for inductive logic programming, which is a subfield of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The focus of the paper is on learning the semantics of programming languages, which falls under the category of programming languages (cs.PL). The paper also uses the Metagol meta-interpretive learning system, which is a machine learning technique, placing it under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper discusses the challenges of the scenario, which includes learning non-observed predicates and abstracting over function symbols, which are topics in software engineering (cs.SE) and computational logic (cs.CL), respectively.
